Linear Regression

The linear regression model was:

rs188247550_T_C_T ~ rs58542926_T_C_T

The samples originate from the genotype dataset with identifier FTD, comprising 337.466 observations. The extracted genotype datasets were stored in genotype_rs58542926_T_C.raw and genotype_rs188247550_T_C.raw, respectively.


Genotype vs.genotype plot

Note that rs58542926_T_C does not contain imputed values! The marker rs188247550_T_C contains 13166 imputed values.


Some metrics obtained using lm():

  • sigma is the estimatimated standard deviation of the noise term
  • Fstat is the value of the F-statistic
  • Rsquared is coefficient of determination
  • Rsq.adj is coefficient of determination adjusted for the number of predictors
  • \(\beta\) is the slope of the regression line
  • CI_low is the lower limit of the confidence interval for \(\beta\)
  • CI_up is the upper limit of the confidence interval for \(\beta\)

Histogram for the magnitudes of the residuals

According to the linear model established, the residuals should be normally distributed. Consequently, the histogram below should approximately resemble a normal distribution.


Normal Q-Q plot of the residuals

This plot shows if residuals are normally distributed. It is desirable that the points displaying the residuals are located close to the straight line.
